Trivy is a vulnerability scanner for containers. To install Trivy on CentOS, you can follow these steps:

Open the terminal on your CentOS system.
Add the Trivy repository to your system by running the following command:

sudo rpm -ivh https://github.com/aquasecurity/trivy/releases/download/v0.40.0/trivy_0.40.0_Linux-64bit.rpm

Note: You can replace the version number in the URL with the latest release version available on the Trivy GitHub releases page.

Once the repository is added, update your system by running the following command:

sudo yum update

Install Trivy by running the following command:

sudo yum install trivy

Verify that Trivy is installed and working properly by running the following command:

trivy --version

This should display the version number of Trivy installed on your system. You can now use Trivy to scan your containers for vulnerabilities.
